<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>She was known for being one of the closest pals to the Kardashian clan. </p>

<p>But Larsa Pippen made sure the spotlight was well and truly on her on Thursday evening as she headed out for dinner at Olivetta in West Hollywood.  </p>

<p>The bombshell, 46, displayed her killer curves in form-fitting snakeskin trousers and a leather-look bustier top as she arrived at the eatery.</p>

<p>Sizzling: Larsa Pippen made sure the spotlight was well and truly on her on Thursday evening as she headed out for dinner at Olivetta in West Hollywood </p>

<p>Larsa - who is the ex-wife of NBA star Scottie Pippen - opted for a pair of stylish perspex heels and added a touch of glamour with a leather mini bag. </p>

<p>The mother-of-four styled her caramel tresses in a sleek straight 'do and opted for a natural make-up that highlighted her stunning features. </p>

<p>Larsa completed her dinner date look with large hoop earrings and a blingy watch. </p>

<p>All eyes on her: The bombshell, 46, displayed her killer curves in form-fitting snakeskin trousers and a leather-look bustier top as she arrived at the eatery</p>

<p>Hourglass: Larsa - who is the ex-wife of NBA star Scottie Pippen - opted for a pair of stylish perspex heels and added a touch of glamour with a leather mini bag</p>

<p>Larsa had a rumoured fall out with the Kardashian family earlier this year as Kourtney and Khloe unfollowed her on Instagram amid Kanye West's Twitter meltdown.</p>

<p>The dramatic unfollowing was seemingly prompted after the rapper, 43, cryptically Tweeted: 'Larsa,' along with a thinking face emoji, followed by the question: 'Should I name more?' </p>

<p>Larsa appeared to respond by unfollowing the famous sisters, including her BFF Kim. </p>

<p>The following morning she appeared to address the rumours as she shared a post in which she revealed she was: 'praying that everybody finds peace'. </p>

<p>Work it: Larsa completed her dinner date look with large hoop earrings and a blingy watch </p>

<p>Kim recently announced the end of Keeping Up With The Kardashians, in which Larsa was a show regular.  </p>

<p>The reality TV series has followed the lives of the family – including sisters Kourtney, 41, Kim, 39, and Khloe, 36, half sisters Kendall, 24, and Kylie Jenner, 23, brother Rob, 33, and mother Kris Jenner, 64 – for 20 seasons aired over the past 14 years.</p>

<p>However, it has now been confirmed the show will be coming to an end with the 21st season in early 2021.</p>

